snippet: Spain striker Jese scored in injury time as his team came from behind to beat Mexico, 2-1, in Istanbul to set up a quarterfinal against Uruguay at the Under-20 World Cup.
abstract: Spain beats Mexico, 2-1, in Istanbul to set up a quarterfinal against Uruguay at soccer's Under-20 World Cup.
lead_paragraph: Spain striker Jese scored in injury time as his team came from behind to beat Mexico, 2-1, in Istanbul to set up a quarterfinal against Uruguay at the Under-20 World Cup.
